Etymology[edit]

From receptus +‎ -ō

Pronunciation[edit]

  • (Classical) IPA(key): /reˈkep.toː/, [rɛˈkɛp.t̪oː]
  • (Ecclesiastical) IPA(key): /reˈt͡ʃep.to/, [rɛˈt͡ʃɛp.t̪ɔ]

Verb[edit]

receptō (present infinitive receptāre, perfect active receptāvī, supine receptātum); first conjugation

  1. to recover.
